{"questionId":"14622120","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the area of triangle <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>AOB</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>)</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>124</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>996</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use area of triangle formula&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>2</mn></mfrac><mo>×</mo><mn>25</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>36</mn><mo>×</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo> </mo><mo>(</mo><mn>124</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>996</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>°</mo><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>67</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>67</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4700</mn><mo>…</mo><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>)</mo></math> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong> A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Units are required. The final <em><strong>A1</strong></em> is only awarded if the correct units are seen in their answer; hence award&nbsp;<em><strong>(A1)(M1)(A1)A0</strong> </em>for an unsupported answer of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>67</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5</mn></math>. Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>67</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>4670</mn><mo>…</mo><mo> </mo><msup><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">m</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> from use of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>3</mn></math> sf values.</p>\n<p>Full follow through marks can be awarded for this part even if their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">O</mi><mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">A</mi><mo>^</mo></mover><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">B</mi></math> is not obtuse, provided that all working is shown.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"14622120","referenceCode":"23M.2.SL.TZ2.1b","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Calculate the area of triangle AOB.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}